We’ll show that, based on the given facts, no chain of “ancestor‐descendant” links can be found that relates Janet and Russell in any of the four candidate ways. (For example, one might suspect that one is in the direct ancestral line of the other or that they might share a descendant or an ancestor, but careful examination reveals no such connection.) 

For instance, the only provided fact with Janet is “Anthony is Janet’s ancestor” (and, by additional links, Janet is in the “Anthony” branch of one family tree). In contrast the only fact with Russell is “Russell is Julia’s ancestor” (placing him in an entirely separate branch of the picture). There are no links given between Anthony (or any of Janet’s other known ancestors) and Russell (or any of his known descendants). 

Thus, none of the options (sharing a common descendant; Janet being Russell’s ancestor; Janet being Russell’s descendant; or Janet and Russell sharing a common ancestor) is supported by the information provided.

<ANSWER>5</ANSWER>
